Operatives of the Kwara State Command, Nigeria Security and Civil Defense Corps, NSCDC have arrested a 42-year-old man, Abdulsalam Ajibola for alleged impersonation. Spokesman of the Command, Ayeni Olasunkanmi disclosed that the suspect was tracked down at Oke-Onigbin, in Isin Local Government Area of Kwara State on the 24th of March,2023 by the tracking Unit of the Command. The suspect allegedly impersonated a Soldier to defraud Abdullahi Saheed of N700,000 and Ropo Gabriel to the tune of N96,000 having promised to help them get admission into Nigeria Defence Academy (NDA), Kaduna. He was also alleged to have falsely taken a Toyota Picnic car from one Prophet Samuel Olugbemiga for Commercial transportation after which he absconded. The spokesman said the suspect will be arraigned before the law court for prosecution.